<subSubSection id="C30C6553A329FFFBFF5EFB4DFE80FA2D" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA936D8A329FFFBFF5EFB4DFE2FFAEA" blockId="31.[151,1436,1261,1540]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B962EACAA329FFFBFF5EFB4DFEFAFABD" bold="true" box="[151,274,1261,1287]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males and females with scopula of tarsi and metatarsi laterally extended, giving a spatulate appearance, in conjunction with anterior row of eyes straight or slightly procurve and 1 to 3 distal spines ventrally on tibiae and/or metatarsi III and IV.
</paragraph>
